WEBVTT

00:02.033 --> 00:05.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The White House
isn't saying tonight whether
tape recordings do exist of

00:05.733 --> 00:09.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump's
conversations with former
FBI Director James Comey.

00:09.366 --> 00:14.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Over the weekend, several
Republican senators
urged the president to
answer that question,

00:14.966 --> 00:16.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
yes or no.

00:16.966 --> 00:20.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the White House
today, reporters pressed
Press Secretary Sean
Spicer on the subject.

00:20.533 --> 00:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House
Press Secretary: I think the
president made it very clear on

00:23.133 --> 00:28.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
