he goes before a Senate
committee tomorrow.

00:42.800 --> 00:47.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Sessions faces questions
about his contacts with
Russia's ambassador
during the presidential

00:48.300 --> 00:50.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
race.

00:50.333 --> 00:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A second U.S. appeals court
has upheld a block on President
Trump's modified travel ban.

00:56.166 --> 01:00.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Seattle today, three judges
of the Ninth Circuit Court
agreed with a ruling by a lower

01:01.700 --> 01:04.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
court in Hawaii that the ban
discriminates against Muslims.

01:04.433 --> 01:09.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A federal appeals court
in Virginia already
issued a similar ruling
in a separate case.

01:11.300 --> 01:13.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The attorneys general of
Maryland and the District of
Columbia charged today that the

01:13.933 --> 01:18.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
president's ongoing business
ties violate the Constitution.

01:18.933 --> 01:23.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They sued in federal court,
citing the Emoluments
Clause, designed to
head off conflicts of

01:24.933 --> 01:27.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
interest.

01:27.366 --> 01:30.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Washington, the two
officials, both Democrats,
said it's a matter
of saving democracy.

01:30.266 --> 01:35.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KARL A. RACINE, D.C. Attorney
General: We're concerned that
foreign governments are coming

01:37.233 --> 01:40.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the Trump businesses for
the single purpose of currying
special favor from the president

01:42.800 --> 01:47.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the United States, so that
their interests can get a higher
priority than the interests

01:48.633 --> 01:50.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the American people.

01:50.633 --> 01:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A White House
spokesman said the suit is
motivated by partisan politics.

01:54.700 --> 01:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A similar lawsuit is
pending in New York state.

01:58.300 --> 02:03.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The White House also condemned
Russia's crackdown today on
protesters against corruption.

02:04.700 --> 02:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
More than a thousand people were
arrested across the country.

02:07.833 --> 02:11.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Alex Thomson of
Independent Television
News filed this report.

02:11.633 --> 02:16.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEX THOMSON: Hundreds arrested
in Moscow alone on a day of
protests nationwide against

02:19.133 --> 02:24.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
corruption generally and
Vladimir Putin particularly.

02:24.000 --> 02:29.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
