and "Russia without Putin"
-- all of this organized by

02:34.500 --> 02:39.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Kremlin's most
prominent critic by
far, the anti-corruption
campaigner and presidential

02:40.233 --> 02:42.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hopeful Alexei Navalny.

02:42.266 --> 02:46.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If Navalny's plan was to rain
on President Putin's parade,
it's certainly succeeding

02:48.066 --> 02:50.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in this part of
the demonstration.

02:50.466 --> 02:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thousands of people gathered
here, plainly the vast majority
of them here pro-Navalny.

02:54.266 --> 02:58.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN (through translator):
Putin is killing our people.

02:58.233 --> 02:59.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's killing you and me.

02:59.966 --> 03:03.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He's sending people to
Ukraine and Syria to
die for his interests.

03:03.333 --> 03:05.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Let's tell him
we're not having it.

03:05.033 --> 03:08.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
I came here for the truth.

03:08.866 --> 03:11.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our government is not
conducting itself properly.

03:11.366 --> 03:16.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEX THOMSON: Navalny was
allowed to demo in Moscow,
just not here, on the main road

03:17.533 --> 03:19.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
leading straight
up to Red Square.

03:19.200 --> 03:22.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But late last night, he
ordered his people to
this illegal location.

03:22.666 --> 03:25.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That made confrontation
inevitable.

03:25.800 --> 03:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Muscovites," he told people
in a late-night appeal,
"come to Tverskaya Street.

03:32.900 --> 03:34.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Don't go anywhere else."

03:34.900 --> 03:39.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Alexei Navalny himself never
made it to his own protest,
arrested at his home in Moscow.

03:42.100 --> 03:47.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He could now be detained
for up to 30 days.

03:49.000 --> 03:52.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Across Moscow, as across
Russia, these were the official
independence day celebrations,

03:54.533 --> 03:57.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the kind the Kremlin wanted
people to see and, let's
face it, most Russians.

03:57.800 --> 03:59.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Putin remains hugely popular.

03:59.933 --> 04:02.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Navalny's support runs
at just 2 percent.

04:02.566 --> 04:07.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
I don't think protesting
today makes any sense.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People are celebrating.

04:08.033 --> 04:09.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They're happy.

04:09.033 --> 04:11.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Why spoil the mood?

04:11.533 --> 04:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEX THOMSON: This was
Vladivostok demonstrations
and arrests well before
most of Moscow had

04:17.100 --> 04:20.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
even got up this morning,
north to Siberia, Novosibirsk,
and another of more than 200

04:22.933 --> 04:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cities where anti-corruption
protesters gathered, and
west to St. Petersburg,
the same pattern,

04:29.133 --> 04:31.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
gathering chanting
and arresting.

04:31.866 --> 04:36.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And back in this
country, newly elected Montana
Congressman Greg Gianforte

04:38.266 --> 04:42.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
